              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 6 gram of high purity Ho2O3 powder(natural",
                "isotopic composition) was pressed at 10 ton/cm2, and",
                "a pellet, around 0.2 cm thick and 2.0 cm in diameter",
                "was obtained. Monitor foils (Nb, 99.99% pure, 0.5 mm",
                "thick) of the same diameter as the pellets were then",
                "attached in front and at the back of each sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The crystal geometry is 70.1 x 72.3 mm in",
                "diameter and length. The relative efficiency is about",
                "68%, and energy resolution is 1.69 keV at 1332 keV",
                "gamma ray from Co-60. The efficiency of the detector",
                "was pre-calibrated using various standard gamma",
                "sources, which were Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133,",
                "Cs-137, Eu-152, Am-241 and Ra-226."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " During irradiation, the neutron flux was",
                "monitored by a Au-Si surface barrier detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted about",
                "60 min with a yield around 3E10 to 4E10 n/s. The",
                "groups of samples were placed at 0deg. or 135deg.",
                "angles relative to the beam direction and centered",
                "about the T-Mo target at distances of around 4 cm.",
                "The Au-Si surface barrier detector used in 135 degree",
                "that accompanied the alpha-particle tube was at a",
                "distance of 110 cm from the target as neutron flux",
                "monitor."
              ]
            }
          ],
